{
    "chapter": 83,
    "verses": {
        "1": {
            "verses": {
                "83:1": {
                    "id": 1
                }
            },
            "resource_id": 125,
            "resource_name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
            "language_id": 38,
            "slug": "en_jalalayn",
            "translated_name": {
                "name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
                "language_name": "english"
            },
            "text": "<h2>Woe (waylun: a term entailing chastisement; or [it is the name of] a valley in Hell) to the defrauders:</h2>"
        },
        "2": {
            "verses": {
                "83:2": {
                    "id": 2
                }
            },
            "resource_id": 125,
            "resource_name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
            "language_id": 38,
            "slug": "en_jalalayn",
            "translated_name": {
                "name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
                "language_name": "english"
            },
            "text": "<p>those who, when they take measure from people, demand [it] in full, the measure;</p>"
        },
        "3": {
            "verses": {
                "83:3": {
                    "id": 3
                }
            },
            "resource_id": 125,
            "resource_name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
            "language_id": 38,
            "slug": "en_jalalayn",
            "translated_name": {
                "name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
                "language_name": "english"
            },
            "text": "<p>but [who] when they measure for them or weigh for them, they cause [them] loss, they diminish [for them] the measure or the weight.</p>"
        },
        "4": {
            "verses": {
                "83:4": {
                    "id": 4
                }
            },
            "resource_id": 125,
            "resource_name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
            "language_id": 38,
            "slug": "en_jalalayn",
            "translated_name": {
                "name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
                "language_name": "english"
            },
            "text": "<p>Do such [individuals] not know for certain (al indicates an interrogative of rebuke) that they will be resurrected</p>"
        },
        "5": {
            "verses": {
                "83:5": {
                    "id": 5
                }
            },
            "resource_id": 125,
            "resource_name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
            "language_id": 38,
            "slug": "en_jalalayn",
            "translated_name": {
                "name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
                "language_name": "english"
            },
            "text": "<p>for an awful day, that is to say, on it, and this is the Day of Resurrection,</p>"
        },
        "6": {
            "verses": {
                "83:6": {
                    "id": 6
                }
            },
            "resource_id": 125,
            "resource_name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
            "language_id": 38,
            "slug": "en_jalalayn",
            "translated_name": {
                "name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
                "language_name": "english"
            },
            "text": "<p>a day when (yawma is a substitution for the [syntactical] locus of li-yawmin, `to an [awful] day', and as such is in the accusative because of [the verb] mab`thna, `will be resurrected') mankind will rise, from their graves, before the Lord of the Worlds?, [the Lord of] all creatures, for His affair, His reckoning and His requital.</p>"
        },
        "7": {
            "verses": {
                "83:7": {
                    "id": 7
                }
            },
            "resource_id": 125,
            "resource_name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
            "language_id": 38,
            "slug": "en_jalalayn",
            "translated_name": {
                "name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
                "language_name": "english"
            },
            "text": "<p>Nay!, verily, the record of the profligates, that is to say, the record of the deeds of the disbelievers, is in Sijjn — this is said to be a book containing [the record of] all the deeds of the devils and the disbelievers; but it is also said to be a location in the lowermost part of the seventh earth, the place of Satan and his hosts.</p>"
        },
        "8": {
            "verses": {
                "83:8": {
                    "id": 8
                }
            },
            "resource_id": 125,
            "resource_name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
            "language_id": 38,
            "slug": "en_jalalayn",
            "translated_name": {
                "name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
                "language_name": "english"
            },
            "text": "<p>And what would tell you what Sijjn is?, what the book of Sijjn is.</p>"
        },
        "9": {
            "verses": {
                "83:9": {
                    "id": 9
                }
            },
            "resource_id": 125,
            "resource_name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
            "language_id": 38,
            "slug": "en_jalalayn",
            "translated_name": {
                "name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
                "language_name": "english"
            },
            "text": "<h2>[It is] a sealed book.</h2>"
        },
        "10": {
            "verses": {
                "83:10": {
                    "id": 10
                }
            },
            "resource_id": 125,
            "resource_name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
            "language_id": 38,
            "slug": "en_jalalayn",
            "translated_name": {
                "name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
                "language_name": "english"
            },
            "text": "<h2>Woe to the deniers on that day,</h2>"
        },
        "11": {
            "verses": {
                "83:11": {
                    "id": 11
                }
            },
            "resource_id": 125,
            "resource_name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
            "language_id": 38,
            "slug": "en_jalalayn",
            "translated_name": {
                "name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
                "language_name": "english"
            },
            "text": "<p>who deny the Day of Judgement, [the Day of] Requital (alladhna yukadhdhibna bi-yawmi'l-dn: either a substitution for or an explication of al-mukadhdhibna, `the deniers');</p>"
        },
        "12": {
            "verses": {
                "83:12": {
                    "id": 12
                }
            },
            "resource_id": 125,
            "resource_name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
            "language_id": 38,
            "slug": "en_jalalayn",
            "translated_name": {
                "name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
                "language_name": "english"
            },
            "text": "<p>and none deny it but every sinful (the form [athm] is hyperbolic) transgressor, overstepping the bounds.</p>"
        },
        "13": {
            "verses": {
                "83:13": {
                    "id": 13
                }
            },
            "resource_id": 125,
            "resource_name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
            "language_id": 38,
            "slug": "en_jalalayn",
            "translated_name": {
                "name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
                "language_name": "english"
            },
            "text": "<p>When Our signs, [of] the Qur'n, are recited to him, he says, `[Mere] fables (astr) of the ancients!', [mere] tales that were written down (sutirat) in ancient times (astr is the plural of ustra or istra).</p>"
        },
        "14": {
            "verses": {
                "83:14": {
                    "id": 14
                }
            },
            "resource_id": 125,
            "resource_name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
            "language_id": 38,
            "slug": "en_jalalayn",
            "translated_name": {
                "name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
                "language_name": "english"
            },
            "text": "<p>No indeed! — a deterrent and a warning against saying such [things]. Rather there has slayed, engulfed, their hearts, covering them like rust that which they earned, of acts of disobedience.</p>"
        },
        "15": {
            "verses": {
                "83:15": {
                    "id": 15
                }
            },
            "resource_id": 125,
            "resource_name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
            "language_id": 38,
            "slug": "en_jalalayn",
            "translated_name": {
                "name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
                "language_name": "english"
            },
            "text": "<p>Nay!, verily, they, on that day, the Day of Resurrection, will be screened off from their Lord, and so they will not see Him.</p>"
        },
        "16": {
            "verses": {
                "83:16": {
                    "id": 16
                }
            },
            "resource_id": 125,
            "resource_name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
            "language_id": 38,
            "slug": "en_jalalayn",
            "translated_name": {
                "name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
                "language_name": "english"
            },
            "text": "<p>Then they will be exposed to Hell-fire, [then] they will enter the scorching Fire;</p>"
        },
        "17": {
            "verses": {
                "83:17": {
                    "id": 17
                }
            },
            "resource_id": 125,
            "resource_name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
            "language_id": 38,
            "slug": "en_jalalayn",
            "translated_name": {
                "name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
                "language_name": "english"
            },
            "text": "<p>then it will be said, to them: `This, that is, the chastisement, is that which you used to deny!'</p>"
        },
        "18": {
            "verses": {
                "83:18": {
                    "id": 18
                }
            },
            "resource_id": 125,
            "resource_name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
            "language_id": 38,
            "slug": "en_jalalayn",
            "translated_name": {
                "name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
                "language_name": "english"
            },
            "text": "<p>Nay!, verily, the record of the pious, that is, the record of the deeds of the believers who were sincere in their faith, is in `Illiyyn — this is said to be the book [containing] all the good deeds of the angels and the believers from among the two heavy ones [sc. mankind and jinn]; but it is also said to be a place below the Throne in the seventh heaven;</p>"
        },
        "19": {
            "verses": {
                "83:19": {
                    "id": 19
                }
            },
            "resource_id": 125,
            "resource_name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
            "language_id": 38,
            "slug": "en_jalalayn",
            "translated_name": {
                "name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
                "language_name": "english"
            },
            "text": "<p>and what will tell you, [what will] inform you, what `Illiyyn is?, what the book of `Illiyyn is.</p>"
        },
        "20": {
            "verses": {
                "83:20": {
                    "id": 20
                }
            },
            "resource_id": 125,
            "resource_name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
            "language_id": 38,
            "slug": "en_jalalayn",
            "translated_name": {
                "name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
                "language_name": "english"
            },
            "text": "<h2>[It is] a sealed book,</h2>"
        },
        "21": {
            "verses": {
                "83:21": {
                    "id": 21
                }
            },
            "resource_id": 125,
            "resource_name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
            "language_id": 38,
            "slug": "en_jalalayn",
            "translated_name": {
                "name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
                "language_name": "english"
            },
            "text": "<h2>witnessed by those brought near, from among the angels.</h2>"
        },
        "22": {
            "verses": {
                "83:22": {
                    "id": 22
                }
            },
            "resource_id": 125,
            "resource_name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
            "language_id": 38,
            "slug": "en_jalalayn",
            "translated_name": {
                "name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
                "language_name": "english"
            },
            "text": "<h2>Assuredly the pious will be amid bliss, [in] Paradise,</h2>"
        },
        "23": {
            "verses": {
                "83:23": {
                    "id": 23
                }
            },
            "resource_id": 125,
            "resource_name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
            "language_id": 38,
            "slug": "en_jalalayn",
            "translated_name": {
                "name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
                "language_name": "english"
            },
            "text": "<p>upon couches, [upon] beds beneath canopies, gazing, at the bliss which they have been given.</p>"
        },
        "24": {
            "verses": {
                "83:24": {
                    "id": 24
                }
            },
            "resource_id": 125,
            "resource_name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
            "language_id": 38,
            "slug": "en_jalalayn",
            "translated_name": {
                "name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
                "language_name": "english"
            },
            "text": "<p>You will perceive in their faces the radiancy of bliss, the splendour and beauty of blissfulness,</p>"
        },
        "25": {
            "verses": {
                "83:25": {
                    "id": 25
                }
            },
            "resource_id": 125,
            "resource_name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
            "language_id": 38,
            "slug": "en_jalalayn",
            "translated_name": {
                "name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
                "language_name": "english"
            },
            "text": "<p>as they are given to drink a nectar, a wine free of any impurities, [that is] sealed, in its vessel, none other than them breaking its seal,</p>"
        },
        "26": {
            "verses": {
                "83:26": {
                    "id": 26
                }
            },
            "resource_id": 125,
            "resource_name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
            "language_id": 38,
            "slug": "en_jalalayn",
            "translated_name": {
                "name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
                "language_name": "english"
            },
            "text": "<p>whose seal is musk, that is, whose final sip is followed by an emanating scent of musk — so for such [bliss] let the viers vie, let them desire to apply themselves to obedience of God —</p>"
        },
        "27": {
            "verses": {
                "83:27": {
                    "id": 27
                }
            },
            "resource_id": 125,
            "resource_name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
            "language_id": 38,
            "slug": "en_jalalayn",
            "translated_name": {
                "name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
                "language_name": "english"
            },
            "text": "<h2>and whose mixture, that is to say, that with which it is mixed, is of Tasnm, which is explained by His [following] words:</h2>"
        },
        "28": {
            "verses": {
                "83:28": {
                    "id": 28
                }
            },
            "resource_id": 125,
            "resource_name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
            "language_id": 38,
            "slug": "en_jalalayn",
            "translated_name": {
                "name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
                "language_name": "english"
            },
            "text": "<p>a spring (`aynan is in the accusative because of an implicit [prefatory] amdahu, `I extol [this spring]') from which those brought near will drink (yashrabu bih: [should be yashrabu] minh, or [it may be that bih is used because] yashrabu is meant to imply the sense of yaltadhdhu [bih, `in which they delight']).</p>"
        },
        "29": {
            "verses": {
                "83:29": {
                    "id": 29
                }
            },
            "resource_id": 125,
            "resource_name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
            "language_id": 38,
            "slug": "en_jalalayn",
            "translated_name": {
                "name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
                "language_name": "english"
            },
            "text": "<p>Verily the guilty, like Ab Jahl and his ilk, used to laugh at the believers, such as `Ammr [b. Ysir] and Bill [the Ethiopian] and those like them, in mockery of them;</p>"
        },
        "30": {
            "verses": {
                "83:30": {
                    "id": 30
                }
            },
            "resource_id": 125,
            "resource_name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
            "language_id": 38,
            "slug": "en_jalalayn",
            "translated_name": {
                "name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
                "language_name": "english"
            },
            "text": "<p>and when they, the believers, passed them by, they would wink at one another, the guilty beckoned with their eyebrows and eyelids towards the believers in mockery;</p>"
        },
        "31": {
            "verses": {
                "83:31": {
                    "id": 31
                }
            },
            "resource_id": 125,
            "resource_name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
            "language_id": 38,
            "slug": "en_jalalayn",
            "translated_name": {
                "name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
                "language_name": "english"
            },
            "text": "<p>and when they returned to their folks they would return blithely (fkihna: a variant reading has fakihna), rejoicing in their [disparaging] mention of the believers;</p>"
        },
        "32": {
            "verses": {
                "83:32": {
                    "id": 32
                }
            },
            "resource_id": 125,
            "resource_name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
            "language_id": 38,
            "slug": "en_jalalayn",
            "translated_name": {
                "name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
                "language_name": "english"
            },
            "text": "<p>and when they see them, that is, the believers, they say, `Lo! these [men] are astray!', on account of their belief in Muhammad (s).</p>"
        },
        "33": {
            "verses": {
                "83:33": {
                    "id": 33
                }
            },
            "resource_id": 125,
            "resource_name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
            "language_id": 38,
            "slug": "en_jalalayn",
            "translated_name": {
                "name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
                "language_name": "english"
            },
            "text": "<p>God, exalted be He, says: Yet they, that is, the disbelievers, were not sent as watchers over them, [over] the believers, to preserve them or [to keep a record of] their deeds and thus guide them back to what is best for them.</p>"
        },
        "34": {
            "verses": {
                "83:34": {
                    "id": 34
                }
            },
            "resource_id": 125,
            "resource_name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
            "language_id": 38,
            "slug": "en_jalalayn",
            "translated_name": {
                "name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
                "language_name": "english"
            },
            "text": "<p>So today, that is, the Day of Resurrection, the believers will be laughing at the disbelievers,</p>"
        },
        "35": {
            "verses": {
                "83:35": {
                    "id": 35
                }
            },
            "resource_id": 125,
            "resource_name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
            "language_id": 38,
            "slug": "en_jalalayn",
            "translated_name": {
                "name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
                "language_name": "english"
            },
            "text": "<p>upon couches, in Paradise, gazing, out from their dwellings at the disbelievers while they are being tortured; and they will laugh at them just as they, the disbelievers, had laughed at them in the world.</p>"
        },
        "36": {
            "verses": {
                "83:36": {
                    "id": 36
                }
            },
            "resource_id": 125,
            "resource_name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
            "language_id": 38,
            "slug": "en_jalalayn",
            "translated_name": {
                "name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
                "language_name": "english"
            },
            "text": "<p>Have the disbelievers been requited for what they used to do? Yes, indeed! Meccan, consisting of 23 or 25 verses.</p>"
        }
    }
}